  "prompt": "How do petrol pumps earn?",
  "response": "Petrol pumps, also known as fuel stations or gas stations, earn money primarily through the sale of fuel, but there are several other ways they generate income:\n\n1. **Fuel Sales**: The primary source of income for petrol pumps is the sale of gasoline, diesel, and sometimes other types of fuel (like compressed natural gas or ethanol blends). Petrol pumps earn a profit on each liter/gallon sold, although the profit margins per unit of fuel can be relatively small.\n\n2. **Convenience Store Sales**: Many fuel stations have an attached convenience store or mini-mart that sells snacks, beverages, cigarettes, automotive products, and other consumer goods. These stores often have higher profit margins on their products compared to fuel sales.\n\n3. **Car Services**: Some stations offer car maintenance and services such as oil changes, lubricants, car washes, tire repairs, and other automotive services. These services can be lucrative and help attract repeat customers.\n\n4. **Franchise Fees**: For petrol pumps that are part of a larger brand or franchise, they might earn money through franchise fees and receive support and marketing from the parent company.\n\n5. **Advertising**: Some petrol stations might generate additional revenue by leasing space for advertising. This could include signage, billboards, or digital ads displayed on the premises.\n\n6. **Air and Water Service Fees**: Many petrol stations offer air pumps for tires and water for radiators and batteries. While these services are often free, some stations charge a small fee.\n\n7. **Rental Spaces**: Larger fuel stations may rent space to other businesses, such as fast-food chains or coffee shops, thus earning income from leasing agreements.\n\nBy diversifying their services and income streams, petrol pumps can increase their profitability and better serve their customers.",
